HEADWORD: Weasand
<hw>Wea"sand</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wesand</ets>, AS. <ets>w⟦amac⟧send</ets>; akin to OFries.
<ets>w⟦amac⟧sende</ets>, <ets>w⟦amac⟧sande</ets>; cf. OHG.
<ets>weisunt</ets>.]</ety> <def>The windpipe; -- called also, formerly,
<altname>wesil</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Formerly, written also,
<asp>wesand</asp>, and <asp>wezand</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cut his <qex>weasand</qex> with thy knife.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weasel</ent>⟦br⟧
